    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>A collection wherein the constituent parts have in common a general subject, heading, topic, or composition, as distinguished from collections that reflect a common provenance.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000050778/U.S. Library of Congress online (2005-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000061756/Lempel and Soffer, PicASHOW: Pictorial Authority Search (2001)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Een collectie waarvan de samenstellende delen een algemeen onderwerp, titel, thema of samenstelling met elkaar gemeen hebben. Te onderscheiden van collecties die een gemeenschappelijke herkomst vertonen.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Eine Sammlung, worin die einzelnen Bestandteile Schwerpunkt, Oberbegriff, Thema oder Gestaltung miteinander teilen, im Unterschied zu einer Sammlung, die eine gewöhnliche Provenienz spiegelt.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>German</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000232/IfM-SMB-PK</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000122134/IfM Berlin</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>其組成要素均有共同之特定主題、標題、題目、或構成內容的收藏品，與一般來源的收藏品不同。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
